%%{init: {"theme":"base","securityLevel":"strict","deterministicIds":true,"deterministicIDSeed":"lightcode-sso-central-session-v1","themeVariables":{"fontFamily":"Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui","fontSize":"15px","background":"#ffffff","primaryColor":"#f8fafc","primaryTextColor":"#0f172a","primaryBorderColor":"#cbd5e1","secondaryColor":"#eff6ff","secondaryTextColor":"#1e3a8a","secondaryBorderColor":"#93c5fd","tertiaryColor":"#ecfdf5","tertiaryTextColor":"#065f46","tertiaryBorderColor":"#86efac","lineColor":"#64748b","textColor":"#0f172a"}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as Usuario
    participant AppA as App A
    participant AppB as App B
    participant View as /auth/login Views Razor
    participant Auth as HostedAuthOrchestrator
    participant OAuth as OAuthClientRepository
    participant Tx as HostedAuthTransactionRepository
    participant FlowSess as HostedAuthSessionRepository
    participant SSO as SsoSessionRepository
    participant Cookie as Cookie lc_sso
    participant UserStore as Users do tenant
    participant Code as AuthorizationCodeRepository
    participant Token as /api/auth/token
    participant Audit as AuthAuditLogs
    participant Logout as /auth/logout

    AppA->>AppA: Gerar state, nonce, code_verifier e code_challenge S256
    AppA-->>User: Abrir SSO hospedado
    User->>View: GET /auth/login?response_type=code&tenant_id=T&client_id=A&redirect_uri=...&scope=openid email&state=...&nonce=...&code_challenge=...&code_challenge_method=S256
    View->>Auth: StartAsync Authorization Request
    Auth->>OAuth: Validar cliente A, callback exato e scopes
    OAuth-->>Auth: Cliente autorizado
    Auth->>Tx: Criar transacao OAuth curta com state, nonce e PKCE
    Auth->>FlowSess: Criar sessao curta do fluxo no estagio login
    Auth->>SSO: Tentar reutilizar lc_sso existente

    alt Sem sessao SSO valida
        SSO-->>Auth: Ausente, expirada ou revogada
        Auth-->>View: Renderizar login do tenant
        User->>View: POST /auth/login com usuario e senha
        View->>Auth: LoginAsync
        Auth->>UserStore: Validar credenciais, status e politica 2FA

        alt Login exige 2FA
            Auth-->>View: Aguardar 2FA
            View-->>User: Tela /auth/2fa
            User->>View: POST codigo 2FA
            View->>Auth: ConfirmTwoFactorAsync
            Auth->>FlowSess: Completar autenticacao com mfaMethod
        else Login sem 2FA
            Auth->>FlowSess: Completar autenticacao sem mfaMethod
        end

        Auth->>SSO: Criar nova SsoSession por tenant
        Auth->>Audit: sso_session_created
        Auth-->>Cookie: Set-Cookie lc_sso=sessionId; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Lax
        Auth->>Code: Criar authorization code de uso unico vinculado a PKCE
        Auth->>Audit: authorization_code_issued
        View-->>AppA: Redirect redirect_uri?code=...&state=...
    else Sessao SSO valida ja existente
        SSO-->>Auth: SsoSession ativa
        Auth->>UserStore: Revalidar usuario ativo
        UserStore-->>Auth: Usuario ativo
        Auth->>SSO: Atualizar lastSeenAtUtc
        Auth->>Audit: sso_session_reused
        Auth->>Code: Criar authorization code de uso unico para App A
        View-->>AppA: Redirect redirect_uri?code=...&state=...
    end

    AppA->>Token: POST /api/auth/token grant_type=authorization_code + code_verifier
    Token->>Code: Consumir code atomicamente e validar PKCE
    Code-->>Token: Code valido e consumido
    Token-->>AppA: access token + refresh token

    Note over Cookie,Token: JWT e refresh token nunca passam pela view, URL ou cookie SSO.<br/>O cookie lc_sso contem apenas sessionId opaco.

    AppB->>AppB: Gerar novo state, nonce e PKCE S256
    AppB-->>User: Abrir outro app do mesmo tenant
    User->>View: GET /auth/login?...tenant_id=T&client_id=B&prompt opcional&max_age opcional
    View->>Auth: StartAsync nova transacao OAuth
    Auth->>OAuth: Validar cliente B, callback e scopes
    Auth->>SSO: Ler lc_sso e validar tenant, TTL, idle timeout e revogacao

    alt prompt=login
        Auth->>Audit: sso_prompt_login
        Auth-->>View: Ignorar SSO e renderizar login
    else prompt=none sem SSO valido
        Auth->>Audit: sso_prompt_none_failed
        View-->>AppB: Redirect callback?error=login_required&state=...
    else max_age expirado
        Auth->>Audit: sso_session_expired
        Auth-->>View: Renderizar login novamente
    else SSO valido para o mesmo tenant
        Auth->>UserStore: Revalidar usuario ativo
        Auth->>SSO: Touch lastSeenAtUtc
        Auth->>Audit: sso_session_reused
        Auth->>Code: Criar novo authorization code para App B
        View-->>AppB: Redirect callback?code=...&state=...
        AppB->>Token: Exchange code + code_verifier
        Token-->>AppB: Tokens proprios do App B
    end

    User->>Logout: GET /auth/logout?tenant_id=T&post_logout_redirect_uri=...
    Logout->>SSO: Revogar SsoSession atual
    Logout-->>Cookie: Remover lc_sso
    Logout->>OAuth: Validar post_logout_redirect_uri cadastrada
    Logout->>Audit: logout_completed
    Logout-->>User: Redirect pos-logout autorizado

    Note over Auth,SSO: SSO V1 e por tenant.<br/>Sessao SSO expirada, revogada ou com usuario desativado nao emite code.
    Note over Tx,Code: Transacao OAuth, authorization code e PKCE continuam separados da sessao SSO.
